{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton"},"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"Components"}],"platforms":[{"unavailable":false,"name":"iOS","deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"15.0","beta":false},{"introducedAt":"13.0","deprecated":false,"beta":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"macOS"},{"introducedAt":"16.0","deprecated":false,"beta":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"tvOS"},{"introducedAt":"1.0","beta":false,"name":"visionOS","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false},{"beta":false,"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"11.0","name":"watchOS"}],"title":"OUDSButton","externalID":"s:14OUDSComponents10OUDSButtonV","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSButton"}],"roleHeading":"Structure","symbolKind":"struct","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSButton"}]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"@","kind":"attribute"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","text":"MainActor","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSButton","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"mentions","mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Layouts","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Actions"]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Appearances","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Appearances"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Five appearances are proposed for all layouts:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"default (by default)","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Default buttons are used for actions which are not mandatory or essential for the user."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"strong","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Should be singular and prominent, limited to one per view.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It should be reserved for the most critical action, such as “Next,” “Save,” “Submit,” etc. It is a “call for action”.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"brand"}]},{"type":"text","text":": A brand primary color alternative to the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"strong","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" button."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"To be used sparingly for high-value specific actions or to visually anchor a brand moment. Do not use it as the default primary button in your interfaces."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A button with "},{"code":"OUDSButton.Appearance.Brand","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" appearance is not allowed as a direct or indirect child of an "},{"code":"OUDSColoredSurface","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"minimal","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": Minimal buttons are commonly used for actions that are considered less crucial. They can be used independently or together with a strong button."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"negative"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Negative buttons should be used sparingly to warn of a destructive action,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for example, delete or remove, typically resulting in the opening of a confirmation dialog."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A button with "},{"code":"OUDSButton.Appearance.Negative","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" appearance is not allowed as a direct or indirect child of an "},{"code":"OUDSColoredSurface","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Code-samples","text":"Code samples","type":"heading","level":2},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["    \/\/ Icon only with default appearance","    OUDSButton(icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), accessibilityLabel: \"Like\", appearance: .default) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","    \/\/ Or simpler","    OUDSButton(icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), accessibilityLabel: \"Like\") { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text only with negative appearance","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", appearance: .negative,  style: .default) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","    \/\/ Or simpler","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", appearance: .negative) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ A loading button","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", style: .loading) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text and icon with strong appearance","    OUDSButton(text: \"Validate\", icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), appearance: .strong) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text and icon with strong appearance and button taking full width","    OUDSButton(text: \"Validate\", icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), appearance: .strong, isFullWidth: true) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Localizable from bundle can also be used","    OUDSButton(LocalizedStringKey(\"validate_button\"), bundle: Bundle.module, appearance: .strong) { }"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you need to flip your icon depending to the layout direction or not (e.g. if RTL mode lose semantics  \/ meanings):"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["    @Environment(\\.layoutDirection) var layoutDirection","","    OUDSButton(text: \"Button\",","               icon: Image(systemName: \"figure.handball\"),","               flipIcon: layoutDirection == .rightToLeft)"]},{"anchor":"Styles","text":"Styles","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Two style are available:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default (by default)"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": used in the normal usage of button. The aspect of the button changes for  states ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"disabled","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"pressed","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"hovered","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" or normal (i.e. "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"enabled","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":")"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"loading","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": used after button was clicked and probably data are requested before navigate to a next screen or get updated data."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Rounded layout","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Rounded-layout"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Buttons can have rounded layouts to be favored in more emotional, immersive contexts or those tied to specific visual identities.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For standard or business-oriented journeys, keep the default corners.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This evolution addresses the need for flexibility in adapting the design to some brand contexts.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To activate the rounded button behavior, set to true the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hasRoundedButtons"},{"text":" values of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Tuning"},{"text":" object","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in your theme configuration (if the theme exposes this property at init)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Some themes do not have this flexibility like "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SoshTheme"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"WireframeTheme"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Colored surface","level":2,"anchor":"Colored-surface","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If button is placed on colored surface using ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSColoredSurface","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", the default colors (content, background and border) are automatically adjusted to switch to monochrome mode.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Remark: Today it is not allowed to place a Negative nor a Brand button on a colored surface.","type":"text"}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Specific behavior","level":2,"anchor":"Specific-behavior","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For accessibility reasons, if the system settings for reducing motion is enabled, the loading indicator does not move.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For ecodesign reasons, if the device is in low power mode, the loading indicator does not move.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Design documentation","level":2,"anchor":"Design-documentation","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-button","type":"reference","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Themes rendering","level":2,"anchor":"Themes-rendering","type":"heading"},{"text":"Orange","level":3,"anchor":"Orange","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_button_Orange","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Orange Compact","level":3,"anchor":"Orange-Compact","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_button_OrangeCompact"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Sosh","level":3,"anchor":"Sosh","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_button_Sosh","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Wireframe","level":3,"anchor":"Wireframe","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_button_Wireframe","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"3.2.0 (Figma component design version)"}]}],"name":"Version","type":"aside"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0.10.0"}]}],"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Since"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Button is a UI element that triggers an action or event, and is used to initiate tasks or confirming an action."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Button appears in different layouts, styles and states to indicate hierarchy or emphasis.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudsbutton"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"sections":[],"topicSections":[{"title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton\/init(_:tableName:bundle:appearance:style:isFullWidth:action:)","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton\/init(_:tableName:bundle:icon:flipIcon:appearance:style:isFullWidth:action:)","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton\/init(icon:accessibilityLabel:flipIcon:appearance:style:isFullWidth:action:)","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton\/init(icon:accessibilityLabel:tableName:bundle:flipIcon:appearance:style:isFullWidth:action:)","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton\/init(text:appearance:style:isFullWidth:action:)","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton\/init(text:icon:flipIcon:appearance:style:isFullWidth:action:)"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Initializers"},{"title":"Instance Properties","identifiers":["doc:\